<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How Does Blockchain Technology, Specifically Ethereum, Improve Traceability and Provenance in Logistics?</h3>



<p>Blockchain technology, specifically Ethereum, improves traceability and provenance in logistics by providing a transparent and immutable record of every transaction and movement of goods. This enhances accountability, reduces fraud, and ensures the authenticity of products throughout the supply chain.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What Are the Potential Future Applications of Ethereum in Supply Chain Management Beyond Traceability and Decentralization?</h3>



<p>In the realm of supply chain management, Ethereum holds immense potential beyond just traceability and decentralization. It has the ability to streamline processes, enhance transparency, and facilitate smart contracts for seamless transactions.</p>



